learning_outcomes.en:
Upon successful completion of this course, students should 
*	be knowledgeable about cutting-edge research problems, theoretical and methodological approaches and publications in the study of folklore, everyday culture and cultural heritage;
*	be capable of using these contemporary trends in their professional activities;

independent_work.en:
1) Reading responses and other written or oral assignments based on compulsory readings; to be submitted prior to classroom meetings;
2) participation in recap seminars;
Guidelines will be given at the beginning and during the course.
